review_blob:
Appearance: hazy yellow, with two finger head, lots of carbonation. Beautiful in the glass.

Aroma: bready, spice and fruits with a slight alcohol presents.

Taste: very nice and well balanced. Floral tastes with fruity notes. Perfect bitterness, not too much not too little. Perfectly amount of spice tastes as well.

Overall: another excellent Belgian tripel. I have really gotten into Belgian style lately and this is another excellent example.

Appearance: Poured into a snifter, almost no head which giving the ABV comes as no surprise. Pitch black almost a 60 weight motor oil appearance. Seems to coat the glass very well.

Aroma: very complex. Dark fruits, roasted malt, Carmel, hints of coffee and chocolate. A lot going on.

Taste: very nice, up front getting the roasted malts, coffee, caramel malt, dark fruits. The dark fruits aren't as forward as I would have expected given how noticeable they were on the nose, they are more in the background on the palate. The alcohol is nearly undetectable, which is very impressive, though I do get the warmth of it after the swallow.

Overall: awesome brew, this is my first Mikkeller beer and I'm very impressed. Extremely well balanced and enjoyable. Be careful with this the alcohol is so unnoticeable it could get you into trouble real quick.

Appearance: absolutely beautiful, deer amber brown thick off white frothy head with awsome retention.
Aroma: roasted malt, vanilla, coffee a lot going on.
Taste: roasted malt, vanilla, coffee, Carmel, dark chocolate, smokiness.
Palate: very nice, not too thick not to thin.. The lacing is unbelievable.
Overall: very solid porter, would love to pick up more.

Pours a cloudy yellow with thin whit head that dissipates quickly
On the nose there is not much going on bready with a bit of sweetness.
Taste: follows the nose, just not a whole lot going on. Bready mildly sweet thin on the palate.
Overall: hate to say it ,but, I'm disappointed in this, usually SA, while not the highest end craft brew usually puts out some pretty good offerings but this one just missed the mark. It's not bad just not blow your socks of, ooh I have to get more of this, good.

Wonderful brew... I'm getting roasted malt, bourbon, coffee on the nose. Taste more of the same on pallet, with th addition of vanilla and chocolate.. Not heavy and not to thin on the mouth feel... Over all I really enjoyed this brew, will defiantly be picking up more.

Opaque black... Total aroma bomb, bourbon, coffee, chocolate, smoke...
Taste, follows nose perfectly 
Very solid brew, one of the best.. Lives up to the hype perfectly.
beer_name: Goose Island Bourbon County Stout - Coffee
